article.headline: Hampton 66, Norfolk St 52
article.story: HAMPTON, Va. (AP) -- Rashad West scored 21 points as Hampton took a large first-half lead and held on in the second for a 66-52 victory over Norfolk State on Wednesday. The Pirates (13-13, 9-6 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) used a 12-1 run to close the half with a 44-22 lead. The Spartans (8-17, 8-7) used 50 percent shooting in the second half to mount a small comeback, closing to within 10 points with 8:18 remaining. But it wasn't enough. Matthew Pilgrim scored 16 points and Michael Freeman had 10 for the Pirates. Norfolk State's Corey Lyons scored 15 points and Tony Murphy added 11.
